&lt;p&gt;Role Type: Individual Contributor + Team Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Duration: [6 months / Ongoing]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Role Summary&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lob is entering a pivotal new chapter, and we are seeking a visionary Lead Product Designer to scale our product. In this role, you will do more than design features; you will design the systems and UX philosophies that elevate our design org. This is a unique opportunity to take a successful, established company and reimagine its design language for the AI era. You will have the autonomy to challenge old assumptions, and the startup environment to design high-impact features yourself.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leveraging best in class design practices and a deep understanding of JTBD, deliver recommendations that reduce friction across key customer workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the customer advocate. Drive roadmap prioritization conversations that stem from both qualitative and quantitative insights into how customers interact with our product.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Refine Design Team processes with AI at the core - from initial discovery and wireframing to developer handoff - to improve output quality and lead time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Engineering to account for different use cases and edge cases. Raise healthy tension between UX, product scope, and technical feasibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide high-quality, actionable feedback to junior and mid-level designers through structured critique sessions to support design quality and consistency.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Explore AI-first interfaces, including non-linear workflows and proactive system interactions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct design reviews and QA audits to ensure shipped features meet usability and aesthetic standards.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure design system components are accessible, tokenized, and modular.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Qualifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;7+ years of product design experience, with at least 2 years in a leadership capacity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Systems Expert:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;A proven track record of building and scaling design systems&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Portfolio:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;A portfolio demonstrating sophisticated UI/UX work, but more importantly, the documentation and logic behind the systems you&#39;ve built.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mentorship History:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;Experience directly coaching other designers and helping them level up their visual and strategic skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hourly Rate: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;$85 - $100/ per hour&lt;/p&gt;
